Indicators Overview

IndicatorTargetMeasure
CO1: To strengthen health system capacity to prepare, prevent, detect and timely respond to epidemic-prone & endemic diseases, all-hazards emergency risk management and manage the health information system
IN1: Number of consultations for communicable diseases5,000,000910,207calendar_today
CO2: To ensure access to safe, equitable and inclusive humanitarian lifesaving and life-sustaining health services to people in need and the most vulnerable (including IDPs, Women & Children, GBV survivors, Persons with Disabilities (PWDs), older persons, Trauma-affected & Non-Communicable Diseases (NCDs) patients, refugees ,returnees , Muhamasheen & other poor people in the community , at all levels of service delivery, through a quality MSP package with a stronger focus on primary & secondary health care.
IN1: Number of total outpatient consultations12,600,0001,687,015calendar_today
IN2: Number of antenatal care visits2,000,000237,061calendar_today
IN3: Number of total deliveries assisted (Normal & C-Section)625,00076,497calendar_today
CO3: To sustain the functionality of health system at primary and secondary health care levels through the provision of operational cost (electricity, water & oxygen); medicines, medical equipment and supplies, rehabilitation/revitalization of health infrastructure, capacity building and financial support of Health Care Workers (HCW). In addition, establishing adequate referral between the community and primary health care levels to higher levels of service delivery including provision of integrated rehabilitative, advanced trauma and Intensive Care Unit (ICU) at tertiary care level to improve the resilience of health system and& people
IN1: Number of health facilities with operational support3,5000calendar_today
